website_summaries.verdict: All rabbit owners know that our floppy-eared friends love hay, but since alfalfa contains worryingly high levels of calcium and protein, consider this alternative timothy grass hay and nutrition-loaded pellet formula for long-term health instead.
pros: Sun-cured timothy grass hay is the first ingredient
Mix of alfalfa-free hay and high-fiber pellets
cons: While this is a comprehensive diet for adult rabbits 7 months and older, younger rabbits should eat age-appropriate food

I've tried other brands of timothy pellets that my bunnies would not eat. they nearly starved themselves until I mixed alfalfa pellets in- then they picked out the alfalfa one. but they do not do that with these! They gladly eat them and I have been able to cut alfalfa pellets entirely out of their diet. I'm sad I cannot find this brand locally, but thanks to amazon I can still get alfalfa free pellets even in my remote town.

customer_reviews.title: 100% Timothy Hay
customer_reviews.text: My rabbits love this food, and the most important thing is that it's 100% timothy hay! Adult rabbits should not eat food with alfalfa hay or any other filler ingredients, so this is perfect and a good price.
customer_reviews.author: TEP

customer_reviews.title: Rabbit Did Not Like And Found Corn Kernel in Feed
customer_reviews.text: Purchased this for a Flemish Giant Rabbit. Rabbit would not touch this food and consistently dumped her feeding dish. Purchased a different brand that she has liked in the past and mixed the Kaytee feed with it. Rabbit would eat it when mixed. However, today I found a corn kernel in the feed bag. I will not be feeding this to here again and have already destroyed the Kaytee feed.
customer_reviews.author: Travis

customer_reviews.title: Good substitute for Oxbow Hay!
customer_reviews.text: My rabbit is super picky about what she eats and usually won’t eat the food my brothers rabbit has when I run out of the expensive Oxbow! This is a lot better in terms of size and price , and my bunny really didn’t even need an adjustment period before she started gobbling it up ! Definitely will be coming here instead of petsmart.

customer_reviews.title: A lot of dust but good rabbit food to supplement hay & veggies
customer_reviews.text: It has a lot of dust, but is one of the few alfalfa-free timothy based rabbit foods that does not contain a lot of other non-bunny ingredients like soy. I try to feed more hay and fresh greens than pellets, but she is a rescue and behaves distictly unhappy if she doesn't get some, so this is the most reasonable I have found.

customer_reviews.title: My rabbits love these pellets
customer_reviews.text: My rabbits love these pellets. Based on tons of bun research, if you have to feed pellets, these are the healthiest version. product_meta.title: Kaytee Timothy Complete Rabbit Food
product_meta.description: Size:9.5 pounds| Style:pelletsKaytee Timothy Complete Rabbit Food 9.5 pounds.Feeding Instructions : When introducing a new food, begin with a mixture of "old and new" food, gradually increasing the amount of new food over a 7 to 10 day period. This will prevent digestive upsets as well as allowing your pet to adjust to something new. Adjust portions for proper weight maintenance and when feeding additional pets. Discard any uneaten food and clean dish before each feeding.
feature_bullets: High fiber daily diet, supports digestive health
Long strand hay provides complete nutrition
Added vitamins & minerals to maintain overall health
